@node MENU_PROJECT "Project Menu"

@{b}Project Menu@{ub}

  @{b}New@{ub}  (Ctrl+N)
    Close the current project and start a new blank project with
    a single empty screen. Unsaved changes are discarded.

  @{b}Open...@{ub}  (Ctrl+O)
    Open a .petmate project file using the system file requester.

  @{b}Save@{ub}  (Ctrl+S)
    Save the project to its current file path. If the project has
    not been saved before, prompts for a file name.

  @{b}Save As...@{ub}  (Ctrl+A)
    Save the project to a new file path chosen via the file
    requester.

  @{b}Open Recent@{ub}
    Submenu listing the four most recently opened project files.
    Click an entry to open that file directly.

  @{b}Export As@{ub}
    Submenu for exporting the current screen. See @{"Export Formats" link EXPORT}.

  @{b}Import@{ub}
    Submenu for importing external files. See @{"Import" link IMPORT}.

  @{b}Iconify@{ub}
    Minimise the application window to an AppIcon on the Workbench.

  @{b}About@{ub}
    Display version and copyright information.

  @{b}Quit@{ub}  (Q)
    Exit PetMate.

  @{" Back to Menus " link MENUS}

@endnode


@node MENU_EDIT "Edit Menu"

@{b}Edit Menu@{ub}

  @{b}Draw 1@{ub}  (F1)
    Activate the Draw tool. Places characters and colors.

  @{b}Draw 2@{ub}  (F2)
    Activate the Colorize tool. Changes colors only.

  @{b}Draw 3@{ub}  (F3)
    Activate the CharDraw tool. Places characters only.

  @{b}Draw 4@{ub}  (F4)
    Activate the Lasso Brush tool. Capture and stamp brushes.

  @{b}Draw 5@{ub}  (F5)
    Activate the Text tool. Type text directly onto the canvas.

  @{b}Draw 6@{ub}  (F6)
    Activate the Reverse Draw tool. Drag a rectangle to swap
    foreground and background colors in the selected region.

  @{b}Undo@{ub}  (Z)
    Undo the last edit operation. PetMate maintains a circular
    buffer of screen snapshots.

  @{b}Redo@{ub}  (Y)
    Redo the last undone operation.

  @{b}Copy Screen@{ub}
    Copy the entire current screen to the internal clipboard.

  @{b}Paste Screen@{ub}
    Replace the current screen with the contents of the internal
    clipboard.

  @{b}Clear Screen@{ub}
    Fill the entire screen with the current border color, removing
    all characters and resetting cell colors.

  @{b}Shift Left@{ub}
    Shift all screen content one character to the left. Content
    that moves off the left edge wraps to the right.

  @{b}Shift Right@{ub}
    Shift all screen content one character to the right.

  @{b}Shift Up@{ub}
    Shift all screen content one character upward. Content that
    moves off the top wraps to the bottom.

  @{b}Shift Down@{ub}
    Shift all screen content one character downward.

  @{" Back to Menus " link MENUS}

@endnode


@node MENU_SCREEN "Screen Menu"

@{b}Screen Menu@{ub}

  @{b}Add Screen@{ub}
    Append a new blank screen to the project after the current
    screen and navigate to it.

  @{b}Clone Screen@{ub}
    Append an exact copy of the current screen and navigate to it.

  @{b}Remove Screen@{ub}
    Delete the current screen from the project. This action cannot
    be performed if the project contains only one screen.

  @{b}Previous Screen@{ub}  ([)
    Navigate to the preceding screen in the project.

  @{b}Next Screen@{ub}  (])
    Navigate to the following screen in the project.

  @{" Back to Menus " link MENUS}

@endnode


@node MENU_VIEW "View Menu"

@{b}View Menu@{ub}

  @{b}Toggle Grid@{ub}  (G)
    Show or hide a pixel grid overlay on the canvas. The grid
    draws lines around each character cell boundary to assist
    with precise alignment.

  @{b}Charset Upper@{ub}
    Switch the character selector and canvas rendering to the
    PETSCII uppercase character set.

  @{b}Charset Lower@{ub}
    Switch to the PETSCII lowercase character set.

  @{b}Toggle Full Screen@{ub}  (F10)
    Toggle between windowed and full-screen display modes.

  @{b}Open Settings@{ub}  (P)
    Open the project settings window where screen dimensions and
    other project-level properties can be configured.

  @{" Back to Menus " link MENUS}

@endnode


@node MENU_GENERATE "Generate Menu"

@{b}Generate Menu@{ub}

  See the @{"Generate" link GENERATE} section for full descriptions.

  @{b}Random Brush@{ub}
    Fill the screen with random cells drawn from the active brush.

  @{b}Magic Line@{ub}
    Draw algorithmic worm-path line art across the screen.

  @{b}Tron Lines@{ub}
    Generate Tron-style light-cycle corridor patterns.

  @{" Back to Menus " link MENUS}

@endnode


@node MENU_BRUSH "Brush Menu"

@{b}Brush Menu@{ub}

  The Brush menu is only active when a brush has been captured
  with the Lasso Brush tool. See @{"Brush Operations" link BRUSH}.

  @{b}Flip X@{ub}
    Mirror the active brush horizontally (left-right).

  @{b}Flip Y@{ub}
    Mirror the active brush vertically (top-bottom).

  @{b}Rotate 90 CW@{ub}
    Rotate the active brush 90 degrees clockwise.

  @{b}Rotate 180@{ub}
    Rotate the active brush 180 degrees.

  @{b}Rotate 90 CCW@{ub}
    Rotate the active brush 90 degrees counter-clockwise.

  @{" Back to Menus " link MENUS}

@endnode


@node MENU_PALETTE "Palette Menu"

@{b}Palette Menu@{ub}

  Select the active C64 color palette. A checkmark indicates the
  currently active palette. See @{"Color Palettes" link PALETTES} for details.

  @{b}Petmate@{ub}     The original Petmate palette (default)
  @{b}Colodore@{ub}    Measurement-based physically accurate palette
  @{b}Pepto@{ub}       Pepto's measurement-based reference palette
  @{b}VICE@{ub}        The palette used by the VICE emulator

  @{" Back to Menus " link MENUS}

@endnode


